Here's how to implement all three in your `EditProductPage`:

**1 & 2. Intercept back navigation with a confirmation dialog:**

Override `OnBackButtonPressed` (hardware/gesture back) and hook into Shell's `Navigating` event (shell back button):

```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    protected override void OnAppearing()
    {
        base.OnAppearing();
        Shell.Current.Navigating += OnShellNavigating;
    }

    protected override void OnDisappearing()
    {
        base.OnDisappearing();
        Shell.Current.Navigating -= OnShellNavigating;
    }

    // Handles the Shell navigation bar back button
    private async void OnShellNavigating(object sender, ShellNavigatingEventArgs e)
    {
        if (!_hasUnsavedChanges) return;

        // Defer navigation so we can await the dialog
        var deferral = e.GetDeferral();

        bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "You have unsaved changes. Discard them?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (!leave)
            e.Cancel();    // user chose "Stay"

        deferral.Complete();
    }

    // Handles Android/device hardware back button
    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        if (!_hasUnsavedChanges)
            return base.OnBackButtonPressed();

        // Fire-and-forget the async dialog
        ConfirmLeaveAsync();
        return true; // cancel default navigation
    }

    private async void ConfirmLeaveAsync()
    {
        bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "You have unsaved changes. Discard them?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (leave)
            await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
    }
}
```

**3. Custom "Cancel" back button:**

Replace the default back arrow via `Shell.BackButtonBehavior` in your XAML:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.EditProductPage"
             Title="Edit Product">

    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior
            TextOverride="Cancel"
            Command="{Binding CancelCommand}" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>

    <!-- page content -->
</ContentPage>
```

Then in your view model (or code-behind):

```csharp
public ICommand CancelCommand { get; }

public EditProductViewModel()
{
    CancelCommand = new Command(async () =>
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            bool leave = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
                "Unsaved Changes",
                "Discard changes?",
                "Discard", "Stay");
            if (!leave) return;
        }
        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
    });
}
```

**Key points:**
- `e.GetDeferral()` lets you `await` an async dialog inside `Navigating`.
- `OnBackButtonPressed` is synchronous, so you return `true` immediately and handle the dialog in a separate async method.
- `BackButtonBehavior.Command` **replaces** the default back action — the `Navigating` event won't fire for it, so put your confirmation logic directly in the command.
